	   <tr><td colspan=2>I started as a dwarf, but i have paladins of all the the eligible races. As a guideline for each of my paladins, i put as much as i can into str, well not AS much, but a big amount. The i put a little into agi because of the ac penalty if it is under 75. then i put the rest into wis+int for learning skills faster. The result for each was a paladin that could cast fairly well, learned skills VERY fast, and had enough str to carry around plate armor+FS loot. My first character was a dwarf, i put almost all points into int, none into str, a couple into Agi, and about3-5 into wis. The result was a dwarf paladin with 100str, 90dex, 80agi,88wis,88int, and like 55 or so cha. Both of these stat adjustments worked great, but i prefer my first character over all my others.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
