	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I need to stress that you HAVE TO MAKE SURE YOU AGILITY IS AT LEAST 75!! If you run a Dwarf (The best Paladins IMHO) you will not start with a natural agility above 75 (I believe you start at 70...but it's been a while).&nbsp;&nbsp;If your agility is below 75 you suffer a 50 point AC penalty.  I know, I made the ignorant mistake I am advising you not to make. I finally realized that mistake and corrected it with a +6 agility necklace and WHAM, my AC jumped by more than 50 pts just by adding that +6 (and going to 76 agi).  It wasn't hard to fix but now I have to constantly make sure I don't trade items, make changes, etc. that will drop my agility. Learn from my mistake and don't let this happen to you.  <br><br>As for Intelligence for a Paladin? Praetor is right, it is almost useless to put points there. Paladins are Wisdom based casters.  If you want to fight more, put pts on strength and a few on Wisdom. If you want to improve your casting abilities at later lvls, put more on Wisdom and less on Strength.  But keep in mind, in a GROUP setting you are looked on as a tank. You can heal a little too, which is nice, but your main job will be fighting and defending the true casters.  So get your strength up, is my advice....and throw a few extras onto Wisdom once you've made sure about your Agility.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
